ing provider and inform them you are having issues with libpcre2 library on PHP 7.4.'=>'Contact your web hosting provider and inform them you are having issues with libpcre2 library on PHP 7.4.','There is a known issue with PHP version 7.4.x, when using libpcre2 library version lower than 10.33.'=>'There is a known issue with PHP version 7.4.x, when using libpcre2 library version lower than 10.33.','It looks like your server is running PHP version 7.4.x with an outdated PCRE library (libpcre2) that has a known issue with email address validation.'=>'It looks like your server is running PHP version 7.4.x with an outdated PCRE library (libpcre2) that has a known issue with email address validation.','PCRE library issue'=>'PCRE library issue','If you don\'t know how to do the above we strongly suggest contacting your hosting support and provide them the "full Error Log for debugging" below and these steps. They should be able to fix this issue for you.'=>'If you don\'t know how to do the above we strongly suggest contacting your hosting support and provide them the "full Error Log for debugging" below and these steps. They should be able to fix this issue for you.','(If cURL can\'t be enabled on your hosting server) Enable PHP setting: allow_url_fopen, by adding "allow_url_fopen = On" to the php.ini file (without the quotation marks)'=>'(If cURL can\'t be enabled on your hosting server) Enable PHP setting: allow_url_fopen, by adding "allow_url_fopen = On" to the php.ini file (without the quotation marks)','(Recommended) Enable PHP extension: cURL, by adding "extension=curl" to the php.ini file (without the quotation marks) OR'=>'(Recommended) Enable PHP extension: cURL, by adding "extension=curl" to the php.ini file (without the quotation marks) OR','Edit your php.ini file on your hosting server.'=>'Edit your php.ini file on your hosting server.','GuzzleHttp requires cURL, the allow_url_fopen ini setting, or a custom HTTP handler.'=>'GuzzleHttp requires cURL, the allow