 checked, the From Name setting above will be used for all emails, ignoring values set by other plugins.','Force From Name'=>'Force From Name','The name that emails are sent from.'=>'The name that emails are sent from.','If checked, the From Email setting above will be used for all emails, ignoring values set by other plugins.'=>'If checked, the From Email setting above will be used for all emails, ignoring values set by other plugins.','Force From Email'=>'Force From Email','Please note that other plugins can change this, to prevent this use the setting below.'=>'Please note that other plugins can change this, to prevent this use the setting below.','If you\'re using an email provider (Yahoo, Outlook.com, etc) this should be your email address for that account.'=>'If you\'re using an email provider (Yahoo, Outlook.com, etc) this should be your email address for that account.','The email address that emails are sent from.'=>'The email address that emails are sent from.','WP Mail SMTP is a free plugin, and the team behind WPForms maintains it to give back to the WordPress community.'=>'WP Mail SMTP is a free plugin, and the team behind WPForms maintains it to give back to the WordPress community.','As a WP Mail SMTP Pro user you have access to WP Mail SMTP priority support. Please log in to your WPMailSMTP.com account and <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">submit a support ticket</a>.'=>'As a WP Mail SMTP Pro user you have access to WP Mail SMTP priority support. Please log in to your WPMailSMTP.com account and <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">submit a support ticket</a>.','Need support?'=>'Need support?','Alternatively, we also offer <a href="%1$s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">limited support</a> on the WordPress.org support forums. You can <a href="%2$s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">create a support thread</a> there, but please understand that free support is not guaranteed and is limited to simple