se a separate project for your emails, so the project has only 1 Gmail API in it enabled. You will need to remove the old project and create a new one from scratch.'=>'Try to use a separate project for your emails, so the project has only 1 Gmail API in it enabled. You will need to remove the old project and create a new one from scratch.','You may have added a new API to a project'=>'You may have added a new API to a project','Please follow our <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Gmail tutorial</a> to be sure that all the correct project and data is applied.'=>'Please follow our <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Gmail tutorial</a> to be sure that all the correct project and data is applied.','Make sure that the used Client ID/Secret correspond to a proper project that has Gmail API enabled.'=>'Make sure that the used Client ID/Secret correspond to a proper project that has Gmail API enabled.','Make sure that you have Gmail API enabled, and you can do that <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.'=>'Make sure that you have Gmail API enabled, and you can do that <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.','Make sure that Gmail app in your Google Workspace is actually enabled. You can check that in Apps list in <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Workspace Admin</a> area.'=>'Make sure that Gmail app in your Google Workspace is actually enabled. You can check that in Apps list in <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Workspace Admin</a> area.','Make sure that your Google Workspace trial period has not expired. You can check the status <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.'=>'Make sure that your Google Workspace trial period has not expired. You can check the status <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.','There are various reasons for that, please review the steps below.'=>'There are various reasons for that, please review the steps below.','Make sure there is no aggressive caching on site admin area pages or try to clean cache between attempts.'=>'Make sure there is no aggressive caching on site admin area pages or try to clean cache between attempts.','Reinstall the plugin with clean plugin data turned on on Misc page. This will remove all the plugin options and you will be safe to retry.'=>'Reinstall the plugin with clean plugin data turned on on Misc page. This will remove all the plugin options and you will be safe to retry.','Make sure that you are not trying to manually clean up the plugin options to retry the "Allow..." step.'=>'Make sure that you are not trying to manually clean up the plugin options to retry the "Allow..." step.','Authentication code that Google returned to you has already been used on your previous auth attempt.'=>'Authentication code that Google returned to you has already been used on your previous auth attempt.','Please <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read this article</a> to learn more about what can cause this error and follow the steps below.'=>'Please <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read this article</a> to learn more about what can cause this error and follow the steps below.','Unfortunately, this error can be due to many different reasons.'=>'Unfortunately, this error can be due to many different reasons.','Make sure that the generated email has a TO header, useful when you are responsible for email creation.'=>'Make sure that the generated email has a TO header, useful when you are responsible for email creation.','It should be something like this: %1$s. These are incorrect values: %2$s.'=>'It should be something like this: %1$s. These are incorrect values: %2$s.','Check the "Send To" email address used and confirm it is a valid email and was not empty.'=>'Check the "Send To" email address used and confirm it is a valid email and was not empty.','Typically this error occurs because the address to which the email was sent to is invalid or was empty.'=>'Typically this error occurs because the address to which the email was sent to is invalid or was empty.','if you are using Google Workspace, please <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read this article</a> to proceed.'=>'if you are using Google Workspace, please <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read this article</a> to proceed.','if you are using regular Gmail account, please <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read this article</a> to proceed.'=>'if you are using regular Gmail account, please <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read this article</a> to proceed.','Please click "Agree", if you see that button. If not - you will need to enable less secure apps first:'=>'Please click "Agree", if you see that button. If not - you will need to enable less secure apps first:','Go to plugin Settings page and click the "Allow plugin to send emails using your Google account" button.'=>'Go to plugin Settings page and click the "Allow plugin to send emails using your Google account" button.','Make sure that you have clicked the "Allow plugin to send emails using your Google account" button under Gmail settings.'=>'Make sure that you have clicked the "Allow plugin to send emails using your Google account" button under Gmail settings.','You have not properly configured Gmail mailer.'=>'You have not properly configured Gmail mailer.','Google API Error.'=>'Google API Error.','Complete the steps in section "2. Verify Your Domain".'=>'Complete the steps in section "2. Verify Your Domain".','Go to our how-to guide for setting up <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mailgun with WP Mail SMTP</a>.'=>'Go to our how-to guide for setting up <a href="%s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mailgun with WP Mail SMTP</a>.','Typically this error occurs because you have not set up and/or complete domain name verification for your Mailgun account.'=>'Typically this error occurs because you have not set up and/or complete domain name verification for your Mailgun account.','Your Mailgun account does not have access to send emails.'=>'Your Mailgun account does not have access to send emails.','Mailgun failed.'=>'Mailgun failed.','no'=>'no','Contact your web hosting provider and ask them to verify your server can connect to %1$s on port %2$s using %3$s encryption. Additionally, ask them if a firewall or security policy may be preventing the connection - many shared hosts block certain ports.<br><strong>Note: this is the most common cause of this issue.</strong>'=>'Contact your web hosting provider and ask them to verify your server can connect to %1$s on port %2$s using %3$s encryption. Additionally, ask them if a firewall or security policy may be preventing the connection - many shared hosts block certain ports.<br><strong>Note: this is the most common cause of this issue.</strong>','Triple check your SMTP settings including host address, email, and password, port, and security.'=>'Triple check your SMTP settings including host address, email, and password, port, and security.','Your SMTP host is rejecting the connection.'=>'Your SMTP host is rejecting the connection.','Your web server is blocking the connection.'=>'Your web server is blocking the connection.','SMTP settings are incorrect (wrong port, security setting, incorrect host).'=>'SMTP settings are incorrect (wrong port, security setting, incorrect host).','Typically this error is returned for one of the following reasons:'=>'Typically this error is returned for one of the following reasons:','Could not connect to the SMTP host.'=>'Could not connect to the SMTP host.','Enter correct SMTP Username (usually this is an email address) and Password in the appropriate fields.'=>'Enter correct SMTP Username (usually this is an email address) and Password in the appropriate fields.','Enable Authentication'=>'Enable Authentication','Go to WP Mail SMTP plugin Settings page.'=>'Go to WP Mail SMTP plugin Settings page.','This means the connection to your SMTP host was made successfully, but you should enable Authentication and provide correct Username and Password.'=>'This means the connection to your SMTP host was made successfully, but you should enable Authentication and provide correct Username and Password.','Unauthenticated senders are not allowed.'=>'Unauthenticated senders are not allowed.','Verify with them your SMTP account is in good standing and your account has not been flagged.'=>'Verify with them your SMTP account is in good standing and your account has not been flagged.','Contact your SMTP host to ask about sending/rate limits.'=>'Contact your SMTP host to ask about sending/rate limits.','Typically this error is returned when you are sending too many e-mails or e-mails that have been identified as spam.'=>'Typically this error is returned when you are sending too many e-mails or e-mails that have been identified as spam.','This means the connection to your SMTP host was made successfully, but the host rejected the email.'=>'This means the connection to your SMTP host was made successfully, but the host rejected the email.','Error due to unsolicited and/or bulk e-mail.'=>'Error due to unsolicited and/or bulk e-mail.','Verify with your SMTP host that your account has permissions to send emails using outside connections.'=>'Verify with your SMTP host that your account has permissions to send emails using outside connections.','Contact your SMTP host to confirm you are using the correct username and password.'=>'Contact your SMTP host to confirm you are using the correct username and password.','Triple check your SMTP settings including host address, email, and password. If you have recently reset your password you will need to update the settings.'=>'Triple check your SMTP settings including host address, email, and password. If you have recently reset your password you will need to update the settings.','Typically this error is returned when the email or password is not correct or is not what the SMTP host is expecting.'=>'Typically this error is returned when the email or password is not correct or is not what the SMTP host is expecting.','This means we were able to connect to your SMTP host, but were not able to proceed using the email/password in the settings.'=>'This means we were able to connect to your SMTP host, but were not able to proceed using the email/password in the settings.','Could not authenticate your SMTP account.'=>'Could not authenticate your SMTP account.','Contact your web hosting provider and inform them you are having issues making outbound connections.'=>'Contact your web hosting provider and inform them you are having issues making outbound connections.','Could not connect to your host.'=>'Could not connect to your host.','If using "Other SMTP" Mailer, contact your SMTP host to confirm they are accepting outside connections with the settings you have configured (address, username, port, security, etc).'=>'If using "Other SMTP" Mailer, contact your SMTP host to confirm they are accepting outside connections with the settings you have configured (address, username, port, security, etc).','If using "Other SMTP" Mailer, triple check your SMTP settings including host address, email, and password.'=>'If using "Other SMTP" Mailer, triple check your SMTP settings including host address, email, and password.','Contact your web hosting provider and ask them to verify your server can connect to %s. Additionally, ask them if a firewall or security policy may be preventing the connection.'=>'Contact your web hosting provider and ask them to verify your server can connect to %s. Additionally, ask them if a firewall or security policy may be preventing the connection.','Typically this error is returned your web server is blocking the connections or the SMTP host denying the request.'=>'Typically this error is returned your web server is blocking the connections or the SMTP host denying the request.','This means your web server was unable to connect to the host server.'=>'This means your web server was unable to connect to the host server.','This means your web server was unable to connect to %s.'=>'This means your web server was unable to connect to %s.','Could not connect to host.'=>'Could not connect to host.','Ask them to resolve the issue then try again.'=>'Ask them to resolve the issue then try again.','The exact error you can provide them is in the Error log, available at the bottom of this page.'=>'The exact error you can provide them is in the Error log, available at the bottom of this page.','Contact your web hosting provider and inform them your site has an issue with SSL certificates.'=>'Contact your web hosting provider and inform them your site has an issue with SSL certificates.','Typically this error is returned when web server is not configured properly.'=>'Typically this error is returned when web server is not configured properly.','This means your web server cannot reliably make secure connections (make requests to HTTPS sites).'=>'This means your web server cannot reliably make secure connections (make requests to HTTPS sites).','SSL certificate issue.'=>'SSL certificate issue.','Test plain text email was sent successfully! Please check your inbox to make sure it was delivered.'=>'Test plain text email was sent successfully! Please check your inbox to make sure it was delivered.','Test email to %s'=>'Test email to %s','Test failed. Please use a valid email address and try to resend the test email.'=>'Test failed. Please use a valid email address and try to resend the test email.','Send Email'=>'Send Email','You cannot send an email. Mailer is not properly configured. Please check your settings.'=>'You cannot send an email. Mailer is not properly configured. Please check your settings.','Send this email in HTML or in plain text format.'=>'Send this email in HTML or in plain text format.','Off'=>'Off','On'=>'On','HTML'=>'HTML','Send To'=>'Send To','Email Test'=>'Email Test','Settings were successfully saved.'=>'Settings were successfully saved.','Save Settings'=>'Save Settings','Uninstall WP Mail SMTP'=>'Uninstall WP Mail SMTP','Test emails are allowed to be sent, regardless of this option.'=>'Test emails are allowed to be sent, regardless of this option.','You will need to consult with their documentation to switch them to use default WordPress email delivery.'=>'You will need to consult with their documentation to switch them to use default WordPress email delivery.','Some plugins, like BuddyPress and Events Manager, are using their own email delivery solutions. By default, this option does not block their emails, as those plugins do not use default <code>wp_mail()</code> function to send emails.'=>'Some plugins, like BuddyPress and Events Manager, are using their own email delivery solutions. By default, this option does not block their emails, as those plugins do not use default <code>wp_mail()</code> function to send emails.','Do Not Send'=>'Do Not Send','General'=>'General','Misc'=>'Misc','Save Changes'=>'Save Changes','Settings'=>'Settings','Authentication'=>'Authentication','From Email'=>'From Email','From Name'=>'From Name','SMTP Port'=>'SMTP Port','Send a Test Email'=>'Send a Test Email','Encryption'=>'Encryption','SMTP Host'=>'SMTP Host','Return Path'=>'Return Path','Mailer'=>'Mailer','WP Mail SMTP'=>'WP Mail SMTP','Email'=>'Email']];